  "title": "Inventory Management Executive",
  "description": "<p>1. Review and monitor current inventory</p><p>2. Develop a manufacturing schedule to ensure we produce enough products to meet order demand</p><p>3. Collaborate with vendors and sales team to analyze current trends and production needs</p><p>4. Manage excess inventory and determine ways to prevent overproduction</p><p>5. Responsible for products costing (BOM and monthly closing stock valuation)</p><p>7. Manage inter-companies’ transaction related to sales order and purchasing</p><p>8. Contributes to team effort by accomplishing related results as needed</p><p><br /></p><p>Job Requirements:</p><p>- Min. Diploma in Accounting / Business Administration</p><p>- At least 1-2 years related working experience</p><p>- Proficient in English verbal and writing</p><p>- Proficient in Ms. Excel</p>",
